Cell["\<\
These examples are classified to a wrong class with high confidence (this is \
a bad as it can get in terms of classification...). Fortunately, most \
examples in the training dataset are properly classified as shown by the high \
value of the the accuracy.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.815224970445877*^9, 
